<subSubSection type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageNumber="17">
UFES 139 (2 specimens) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Ilhéu">Ilheu</normalizedToken>
Santana, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="São">Sao</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Tomé">Tome</normalizedToken>
. This species of the genus 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:E3955D45-F8D9-42B0-AB1A-2638A2F40D0F" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiesocidae" genus="Apletodon" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Apletodon Briggs 1955:25" order="Gobiesociformes" pageNumber="17" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Apletodon</taxonomicName>
is common on rocks in shallow water at 
<normalizedToken originalValue="São">Sao</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Tomé">Tome</normalizedToken>
and at 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Príncipe">Principe</normalizedToken>
. The species is being described by Fricke (2007), based on animals from 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Príncipe">Principe</normalizedToken>
. We have also frequently seen it at 
<normalizedToken originalValue="São">Sao</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Tomé">Tome</normalizedToken>
Island (Figure 17). The record of 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiesocidae" genus="Apletodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gobiesociformes" pageNumber="17" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pellegrini">Apletodon pellegrini</taxonomicName>
from 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Annobón">Annobon</normalizedToken>
Island/Equatorial Guinea, by Briggs (1990) may have been based on this species. The first author has recently (February 2007) collected this species near Limbe, Cameroon.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
